{
  "texts": [
    "In the latter case, however, there are good reasons to think that it is not the statistics to blame, but the model that ignores non-disc contributions to the broad band flux (e.g.",
    "BLR emission blended with disc emission).",
    "Machine Learning is another novel technology that could in fact help with achieving control over the systematics.",
    "However, apart from a handful of exploratory works, machine learning methods applied to microlensing have remained largely untapped.",
    "Key applications where such methods could make a difference would be fast generation of magnification maps and/or light curves for any κ, γ, κ *, and source size, or direct inference of the model parameters (source size and geometry, κ *, etc) from the data, avoiding expensive Bayesian likelihood estimations."
  ]
}